cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.IR 

The paper focuses on the problem of person recognition from ear images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The challenge involves analyzing the performance of existing techniques, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also mentions sensitivity to occlusions and performance bias on sub-groups of subjects, which could fall under computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) and information retrieval (cs.IR), respectively.
